  "dct:description": "This guide explains how to use and extend NOMADs base sections to create custom schemas for scientific data modeling. Built on an entity-activity framework, base sections such as Entity, Activity, Process, Measurement, and System provide reusable structure and semantics. The documentation details their inheritance, composition, and UML-based relationships, offering practical guidance for implementing lab instruments, materials, experiments, and processes. It also introduces the ReadableIdentifiers section for generating human-readable lab IDs and the nomad-material-processing plugin for specialized use cases.",
